Reasoning: The paper deals with network data and graph analysis, which are common topics in computer science. The focus on recovering the metric structure of a hidden domain from an observed graph suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The use of filtering processes and denoising approaches suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Signal Processing (cs.SI). The analysis of the network model and the recovery of the metric structure may involve numerical algorithms and optimization techniques, which are relevant to the sub-category of Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). The use of the Jaccard index and the theoretical understanding of its denoising properties suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Information Theory (cs.IT).
